HEADWORD: pastime
<hw>pas"time`</hw> <pr>(p⟦adot⟧s"t⟦imac⟧m`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pass</ets> + <ets>time</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>passetemps</ets>.]</ety> <def>That which amuses, and serves to make
time pass agreeably; sport; amusement; diversion; <as>as, that great
American <ex>pastime</ex>, baseball</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

